Sample Problems
1. Tickets for a play were $2 for each child and $4 for each adult. At one showing of the play, one adult brought 4 children and the remaining adults brought 2 children each. The total ticket sales from the children and adults was $60. How many children and adults attended the play?

2. The Bud Brother's Flower Shop is getting ready for the All Soul's Day. They want to make five (5) identical flower arrangements. They have $610 to spend on this type of arrangement and want 24 flowers for each arrangement. Tulips cost $4 each, lilies cost $3 each and orchids, $6 each. They want to have twice as many orchid flowers as the other two flowers combined in each arrangement. How many orchids, tulips, and lilies are there in each arrangement?